http://linguistlist.org/issues/emailmessage/verification.cfm?iss=19-2178.html&submissionid=183963&topicid=3&msgnumber=1  

Full Title: Perspectives in Linguistics 2008 
Short Title: NSPL 2008 

Date: 05-Nov-2008 - 06-Nov-2008
Location: Derpartment of Linguistics University of Kashmir Srinagar India, India 
Contact Person: Nazir Ahmad Dhar
Meeting Email: nazir_dhar@yahoo.com

Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics 

Subject Language(s): English (eng)

Language Family(ies): Indo-European 

Call Deadline: 15-Sep-2008 

Meeting Description:

The Department Of Linguistics University of Kashmir Srinagar India is organising
a two day national seminar on the theme Perspectives in Linguistics 2008. 

Call for Papers

The seminar has the focus to discuss most of the major issues in Linguistics
like General Linguistics, Theoretical Linguistics, Historical Linguistics as
well as Applied Linguistics (Which includes Computational Linguistics, Language
Teaching, Neurolinguistics, Psycholinguistics, NLP, Sociolinguistics,
Anthropological Linguistics, Language and Literature)

The scholars and academicians of eminance from world around are expected to
attend and make presentations in the seminar. The expected participants include
Professor Kristena Beckman (USA), Professor Peter Hook (USA) Professor Hyrean
Lee (Korea), Professor U N Singh, CIIL Mysore, Professor R Gargesh (University
of Delhi), Professor Vaishna Narang Jawahar Lal Nehru (University New Delhi),
Professor R V Dhongde Pune and others. Professor (DR) Riyaz Punjabi Hon'ble
Vice-Chancellor, The University of Kashmir Srinagar will preside over the
inaugural function on 5th November 2008.

The Abstract of the papers (not more than 400 words) should reach to the
department by or before 15th September 2008. The academic committee will inform
after 20th September regarding acceptance of the abstract. Only those
participants will have the right to attend the seminar of international
importance whose abstracts are approved by the academic committee of NSPL.



	
