Date: Tue, 08 Jul 2008 10:30:53
From: Dr. Sonal Kulkarni-Joshi [sonalkulk@rediffmail.com]
Subject: 30th All India Conference of Linguists
E-mail this message to a friend:
http://linguistlist.org/issues/emailmessage/verification.cfm?iss=19-2178.html&submissionid=183966&topicid=3&msgnumber=2 
	

Full Title: 30th All India Conference of Linguists 
Short Title: AICL 30 

Date: 26-Nov-2008 - 28-Nov-2008
Location: Deccan College, Pune, Maharashtra, India 
Contact Person: Prof. K.S. Nagaraja
Meeting Email: aicl30pune@gmail.com
Web Site: http://www.lsi.org.in 

Linguistic Field(s): General Linguistics 

Call Deadline: 30-Aug-2008 

Meeting Description:

The year 2008 marks the Golden Jubilee of Post-Graduate Teaching in Linguistics
at the Deccan College and also in India. So far around five hundred students
have completed postgraduation in Linguistics from this Institute. In the same
period around one hundred and fifty research scholars have obtained doctorate
degrees. The 30th AICL will commemorate this significant event and chart the
history and the future of the teaching of Linguistics in India. The conference
is being held at the same venue as the first LSI Conference which was held in
December 1970. The AICL will return to this campus after an interval of
thirty-eight years! 

Call for Papers

We welcome research papers on all aspects of linguistics related to Indian
languages - covering phonetics, phonology, morphology, syntax, semantics,
typology, historical and comparative linguistics, Indian grammatical tradition,
language teaching, language technology and computational linguistics, clinical
linguistics, translation studies, and literacy studies. We particularly invite
survey-articles to (1) assess the teaching of Linguistics in the country, (2)
trace the inception and growth of teaching departments in the country. 

Abstracts:
Abstracts of research papers, not more than one A4 page (minimum margins: 2.5 cm
or 1 inch; font size 12; single spacing) must be submitted both in .pdf and .doc
formats. The abstract should start with the title of the paper, followed by name
of the author(s), email address, affiliation and the abstract. Please send your
abstract to aicl30pune@gmail.com or to the mailing address provided  below,
latest by 30th August 2008. Only abstracts received by this date will be
included in the Souvenir that will be brought out on the occasion. Acceptance of
abstracts will be communicated latest by 1st October 2008.

Travel and Accommodation:
We will provide free accommodation only to the delegates on the Deccan College
campus or in the guest houses/hostels of collaborating institutions. We will
appreciate if participants can get their home institutions to depute them to the
conference. Delegates who wish to have hotel accommodation at their own expense
may contact the Organisers well in advance. A list of local hotels and a
tentative pricelist will soon be posted on the LSI website www.lsi.org.in

Registration Fees:
Indian delegates (LSI members) Rs. 750
Indian delegates (non-members)Rs.1000
Foreign delegates $50
Local delegates	Rs. 250
Students Rs. 500
	
The registration fee may be paid in the form of a demand draft drawn in favour
of the Co-ordinator, AICL30, payable at the Central Bank of India, Deccan
College Extension Counter, Yerawada, Pune, Maharashtra, India.


 





